<p>I am using states to load my modules. Main view area:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!-- Main application view area --&gt; &lt;div ui-view style="margin-top:55px;width:100%;padding-left:3px;padding-right:3px;height:91%"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Main state defined in main application module that loads duiring bootstrapping.</p>  <pre><code>$stateProvider         .state('body', {             url: '/',             abstract: true,             template: '&lt;div ui-view /&gt;'         }); </code></pre>  <p>Module state:</p>  <pre><code>$stateProvider       .state('body.case', {           templateUrl: 'case.html',           controller: 'caseController',           url: 'case',       }); </code></pre>  <p>Navigation is done like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;li&gt;     &lt;a ui-sref="body.case"&gt;          &lt;span class="nav-icon-text"&gt;Case&lt;/span&gt;     &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/li&gt; </code></pre>  <p>After loading main html page I am navigating to Case. Browser shows main.html#/case. If after that I refresh Browser by pressing F5 the case module is trying loading alone with the main module and that causes some problems. Is there a way of either ensure the main module completes its run before anything else is loading or always reload main.html only regardless of any state being selected?</p>  <p>Thanks</p>